6 User Flow
The application presents one stable six-step workspace. Nested tabs keep the
large editors navigable, while every mechanism's explanation remains beside its
controls:

1. Setup — block settings, shift templates, and resident roster.
2. Coverage — leaves/rotators, the night-float overlay, and shift closures.
3. Policies — teams/restrictions, fairness controls, preferences, and points.
4. History — portable config JSON and optional carryover fairness ledger.
5. Review & run — block summary, validation/advisories, and Generate Schedule.
6. Results — Overview, Schedule, Fairness, Audit, and Export workspaces.

The Results workspaces expose solver/quality/coverage status, the customisable
schedule and manual revalidation, per-resident fairness evidence, per-call audit
and assignment rationale, and CSV/Excel/PDF/JSON artifacts. If the model is
infeasible or times out, the UI distinguishes the status and offers the existing
relax-and-retry recovery where applicable.

Resident entry supports an optional canonical matching mode. It uses Unicode
NFKC, whitespace collapse, and casefold only as a comparison key, keeps the first
entered spelling for display/exports, and is off by default. Historical ledger
records are never silently merged; reconciliation remains explicit.

Diagnostics is separate from the six scheduling steps. Its Performance lab runs
bounded synthetic cases only when requested and never mutates the live config,
ledger, or result. Large cases require an explicit confirmation.

Privacy contract: there is no application database or resident-data persistence.
Uploads, results, and generated artifacts live in the active Streamlit session;
the user-owned config and ledger downloads are the portable durable records.
Automatic persistence remains an opt-in deployment extension requiring an
external store and credentials.
