Implementation Progress (2026-07, round 6 review fixes)
- **Weekend guardrail made O(n):** the residual-spread guardrail now models
  `max − min` with two auxiliary variables and `2·n` bounds per role instead
  of `n²` pairwise bounds (identical semantics — a `hi ≥ residual`/`lo ≤ residual`
  pair, `spread = hi − lo`). The guardrail stays ON at every roster size (it is
  a fairness feature, not gated for speed); the cheaper encoding keeps
  department-scale coverage solid, and at a generous solver budget the
  within-role total range converges to ~1 across seeds.
- **Avoid-pair × night float:** the same-day separation RHS is clamped at
  `max(0, 1 − fixed_nf)`. Two avoid-pair residents each covering a *different*
  NF label on the same day (each cell singly covered — a valid config) is no
  longer forced infeasible by a negative right-hand side; their unavoidable
  NF co-presence is accepted rather than crashing the solve.
- **Ledger cleanup:** `block_adjustments` drops the dead global excusal pass
  that the role-aware pass overwrote; a role with no availability weight now
  correctly takes no excusal credit (nothing to balance) rather than falling
  back to a cross-role debit. Ledger tests unchanged.
- Audit `spec_scale` budget raised 30→60 s to match the (deliberately) heavier
  guardrail model; all scenarios pass.

